I

ID - Annotation Interface in com.stardevllc.stardata.api.annotations
This annotation allows you to tell the library that this field is the id of the table.
This will set the Primary Key flag to true as if you used the PrimaryKey annotation
This will also set the auto_increment flag to true as if you used the AutoIncrement annotation and as long as the field is a supported number type
Ignored - Annotation Interface in com.stardevllc.stardata.api.annotations
When annotating a field with this annotation, the library will ignore that field within the table

O

ObjectCodec<T> - Interface in com.stardevllc.stardata.api.interfaces
This is a class to allow parsing of types outside of the default supported types.
To use this class, simply create a class that implements this interface.
Implement the logic for both the encode and decode methods
Then simply annotation your field(s) using the Codec annotation.
Order - Annotation Interface in com.stardevllc.stardata.api.annotations

Row - Interface in com.stardevllc.stardata.api.interfaces.sql
This class represents a Row or a Record in a Table
This is mainly to allow closing the connection to the database as quick as possible as it stores the data in a HashMap based on the column
The values from each database cell are parsed using TypeHandler's for the field/class and any defined ObjectCodec's for the columns
This means that you can case the value from the getObject method to what you know the type to be.
You can also use the other methods to do this for you, they will attempt to parse the values as well depending on the type of value
Please see each individual method for more information

Table - Interface in com.stardevllc.stardata.api.interfaces.sql

Type - Annotation Interface in com.stardevllc.stardata.api.annotations

TypeDeserializer - Interface in com.stardevllc.stardata.api.interfaces.sql
The functional interface for a deserializer in the TypeHandler class
TypeHandler - Interface in com.stardevllc.stardata.api.interfaces.sql
This allows the abiltity to have Java Classes converted automatically to MySQL Types and vica versa
It is up to the implementor to handle the seriazation and deseralization
You can add these handlers to a DatabaseRegistry which will allow it to be used by all databases registered under that Registry
Alternatively, you can add the handlers to SQLDatabase of which it will only be used by tables in that database.
You cannot add them to Table's individually.
TypeSerializer - Interface in com.stardevllc.stardata.api.interfaces.sql
The functional interface for the serializer in the TypeHandler class
